RLTA Inference. RLTA can generalize effectively
to unseen attack goals. When unseen target content is introduced to the trained agent model, the LM agent autonomously generates the corresponding malicious prompt for the target model. This inference process requires only a single forward pass through the agent model. This capability ensures that RLTA can adapt and respond to a variety of scenarios without the need for iterative interaction during the inference phase.
